<!--Takeuchi Highway--><!--Takeuchi Highway--> [[Category:Route 166 (Japan)]] [[Category:大阪府の交通史]] [[Category:Roads in Osaka Prefecture]] [[Category:奈良県の交通史]] [[Category:Roads in Nara Prefecture]] [[Category:Streets in Japan]] <!--jawiki derived wikidata interwikis--> [[zh:竹內街道]] <!--zhwiki derived wikidata interwikis--> [[zh:竹內街道]]

{{Citation needed|date=March 2013|sortkey=道国166たけのうちかいとう}} {{right| [[File:Takenouchi-Touge01.JPG|thumb|none|256px|{{ill|Takenouchi Pass|ja|竹内峠|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takenouchi Pass|qq=}} (at the Osaka-Nara prefectural border). The left side is part of [[:en:Japan National Route 166|Japan National Route 166]], while the right side shows the old highway.]] }} '''Takenouchi Highway''' (竹内街道) is the oldest ancient government road in Japan, stretching from [[:en:Sakai|Sakai]] in [[:en:Osaka Prefecture|Osaka Prefecture]] to the area near [[:en:Nagao Shrine|Nagao Shrine]] in [[:en:Katsuragi, Nara|Katsuragi]], [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara Prefecture]]. Historically, it was known as '''Tajihi Road''' (丹比道).<ref>{{Cite book|lang=ja|title=Osaka no Kaidō (大阪の街道)|year=1989|publisher=Shōraisha|page=66}}</ref>
From the {{ill|Shiratori Intersection|ja|白鳥交差点|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiratori Intersection|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in [[:en:Habikino|Habikino]] to the vicinity of the Takenouchi settlement in Katsuragi, much of the route was designated as [[:en:Japan National Route 166|Japan National Route 166]] in 1974. In 2017, it became the first [[:en:Japan Heritage|Japan Heritage]] site in Osaka.<ref>{{Cite web|lang=ja|title=Japan Heritage Recognition! Japan's Oldest National Route "Takenouchi Highway and Yokooji"|url=http://www.saikonokandou.com/2017/04/1470/|website=Saikonokandou.com|accessdate=2019-04-04}}</ref> Additionally, in [[:en:Taishi, Osaka|Taishi]], major events such as the "Taishi Sacred Lantern Gathering" in spring and the "Takenouchi Highway Lantern Festival" in autumn are held annually.<ref>{{Cite web|lang=ja|url=http://www.town.taishi.osaka.jp/event_info/nenkangyouji1/1534900110524.html|title=FY2018 Annual Events|website=Taishi Town Official Website|publisher=[[:en:Taishi, Osaka|Taishi]]|accessdate=2019-04-07}}</ref>
